    <item>
      <title>Amos 1</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-01/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-01/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;amos-chapter-1&#34;&gt;Amos Chapter 1&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v1&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; The Message of Amos, Shepherd from Tekoa, About Israel at the Time of Uzziah, King of Judah, and Jeroboam Son of Joash, King of Israel,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v2&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; He said,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v3&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; The LORD says,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v4&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; So I&amp;rsquo;ll send down fire on the house of Hazael,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v6&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;6&lt;/sup&gt; The LORD says,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v7&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;7&lt;/sup&gt; So I&amp;rsquo;ll send down fire on the walls of Gaza&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v8&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;8&lt;/sup&gt; I&amp;rsquo;ll eliminate the people from Ashdod&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v9&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt; The LORD says,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Amos 2</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-02/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-02/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;amos-chapter-2&#34;&gt;Amos Chapter 2&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v1&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; The LORD says,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v2&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; So I&amp;rsquo;ll burn the fortresses in Kerioth;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v3&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; I&amp;rsquo;ll eliminate judges from him&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v4&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; The LORD says,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v5&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;5&lt;/sup&gt; So I&amp;rsquo;ll send down fire on Judah&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v6&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;6&lt;/sup&gt; The LORD says,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v7&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;7&lt;/sup&gt; They walk on the heads of the poor in the dust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v8&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;8&lt;/sup&gt; They lie down beside every altar&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v10&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;10&lt;/sup&gt; I was the One that brought you up from Egypt,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v11&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;11&lt;/sup&gt; Then I raised up some of your offspring to be prophets&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Amos 3</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-03/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-03/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;amos-chapter-3&#34;&gt;Amos Chapter 3&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v1&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; Listen to what the LORD says against you, Israel, against the entire family he brought out of Egypt:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v3&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; Can two men walk together unless they&amp;rsquo;ve agreed on their route?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v4&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; Does a lion roar in the woods before it&amp;rsquo;s made a kill?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v5&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;5&lt;/sup&gt; Does a bird fall into a trap on the ground if there&amp;rsquo;s no bait in it?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v6&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;6&lt;/sup&gt; If a bugle blows in the city, won&amp;rsquo;t the people be afraid?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Amos 4</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-04/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-04/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;amos-chapter-4&#34;&gt;Amos Chapter 4&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v1&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; Listen to this, you cows of Bashan living in Samaria,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v2&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; The Lord GOD has sworn by his holiness,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v3&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; You&amp;rsquo;ll leave through the breaches in the walls,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v5&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;5&lt;/sup&gt; Offer a thank offering with yeast in it;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v8&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;8&lt;/sup&gt; So two or three towns would stagger to another to get a drink,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v13&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;13&lt;/sup&gt; The One that builds mountains and creates wind,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Amos 5</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-05/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-05/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;amos-chapter-5&#34;&gt;Amos Chapter 5&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v1&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; Listen to the dirge I&amp;rsquo;m chanting for you, Israel:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v3&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; The city that goes out 1,000 strong&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v4&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; The LORD tells Israel,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v5&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;5&lt;/sup&gt; Don&amp;rsquo;t rely on Bethel or go to Gilgal or Beersheba;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v6&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;6&lt;/sup&gt; Rely on me so you can live,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v8&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;8&lt;/sup&gt; The LORD is the One that made Pleiades and Orion,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v9&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt; He&amp;rsquo;s the One that flashes destruction at the strong&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v10&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;10&lt;/sup&gt; They hate the one that reproves in court;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Amos 6</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-06/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-06/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;amos-chapter-6&#34;&gt;Amos Chapter 6&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v1&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; Misfortune awaits those of you at ease in Zion,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v2&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; Go over to Calneh and look at what happened there;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v3&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; Are you trying to push away the time of catastrophe?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v7&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;7&lt;/sup&gt; You&amp;rsquo;ll be at the front of the exiles;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v8&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;8&lt;/sup&gt; The Lord GOD has sworn by himself,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v9&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt; It will be that, if ten die in one house 10and the relative that comes to dispose of their bodies says, &amp;ldquo;Is anyone else here?&amp;rdquo; any survivor may start to swear, &amp;ldquo;No, . . .&amp;rdquo; But the relative will interrupt, &amp;ldquo;Don&amp;rsquo;t finish your oath. Don&amp;rsquo;t even mention the LORD.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Amos 7</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-07/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-07/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;amos-chapter-7&#34;&gt;Amos Chapter 7&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v1&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; The Lord GOD showed me a vision. He formed a locust swarm after the spring crop sprouted and the king had mowed his share. 2The swarm had finished eating the vegetation, and I said,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v3&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; The LORD changed his mind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v4&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; The Lord GOD showed me another vision: he had called for fire to punish them. It had burned up the depths of the sea and was beginning to burn up the landscape. 5I said,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Amos 8</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-08/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-08/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;amos-chapter-8&#34;&gt;Amos Chapter 8&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v1&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; The Lord GOD showed me a basket of ripe fruit. &amp;ldquo;My people Israel are also ripe—for punishment. I won&amp;rsquo;t spare them any longer. 3The singing at the palace will turn into wailing. There&amp;rsquo;ll be lots of corpses silently thrown out everywhere.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v4&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; Listen to this, you that run over the needy and trample on the humble, 5saying,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v7&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;7&lt;/sup&gt; The LORD has sworn by Jacob&amp;rsquo;s arrogance,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v9&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt; At that time, I&amp;rsquo;ll make the sun go down at noon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Amos 9</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-09/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/cir-library/translations/cnt-ot/amos/chapter-09/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;amos-chapter-9&#34;&gt;Amos Chapter 9&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v1&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; I saw the LORD standing by the altar. He said,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v2&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; Though they dig down to Sheol,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v3&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; Though they hide on top of Carmel,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v4&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; Even if their enemies take them into exile,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v5&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;5&lt;/sup&gt; The Lord Yahveh of Hosts—&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v8&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;8&lt;/sup&gt; I keep my eye on sinful kingdoms and destroy them;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v9&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt; I&amp;rsquo;ll give the command&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;verse&#34; id=&#34;v10&#34;&gt;&lt;sup class=&#34;verse-num&#34;&gt;10&lt;/sup&gt; All the sinners among my people will die by the sword&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
